<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-299-103  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 299 103.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Digital Review  Jan 30 1989 v6 n4 p32(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Ziff-Davis Publishing Co. 1989.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>System grabs 640MB from microwave link. (LeCroy 7900 WaveCorder)(product announcement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Gianatasio, David.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   LeCroy Corp. (product introduction).andO;Product:   LeCroy 7900 WaveCorder (Data capture device) (productintroduction).andO;Topic:     Microwave CommunicationsData Capture DevicesIntelligence-GatheringMilitaryMarketing StrategyProduct Introduction.andO;Feature:   illustrationphotograph.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>System Grabs 640MB from Microwave LinkandM;CHESTNUT RIDGE, N.Y.andP;  -- LeCroy has unveiled a digital waveform recording andplayback system that company officials claim can capture more than threeseconds (640MB) of continuous data from two analog signals.andM;The product is aimed primarily at the defense and intelligence communities,said Mike Green, a project engineer at LeCroy.andP;  The system lets users &quot;grab achunk [of information] from a microwave link&quot; for analysis, he said.andM;It also lets users isolate points of interest as the data is collected, andit allows them to analyze the events preceding and following those points.andM;The 7900 WaveCorder supports VAXes, VME-based systems and IBM PC AT hosts.andM;The product, priced from $100,000 to $50,000, was scheduled to be shipped tobeta-test sites before the end of the month.andP;  Orders are now being taken forthe product, Green said.andM;For additional information, LeCroy Corp. can be contacted at 700 ChestnutRidge Road, Chestnut Ridge, NY 10977, (914) 425-2000.andO;</TEXT></DOC>